y-7=2(x+1)
(3-6h+3h^2+4-4h-7)\, =\, 3h^2 - 10h,\; \text{ and not} \;\;3h^2 + 2h:
y - 7 = {-10}(x +1) \;\iff \;y = -10x-3
\begin{align} f'(-1) &= \lim_{h\to 0} \frac{f(-1 + h) - f(-1)}{h} \\  &= \lim_{h\to 0} \frac{3(-1+h)^2 + 4 - 4h - 7}{h}\\ &= \lim_{h\to 0}\frac{3 - 6h + 3h^2 -4h - 3}{h}\\ &=\lim_{h\to 0}\frac{h(-10 + 3h)}{h}\\ &=\lim_{h\to 0} -10 + 3h = -10. \end{align} 
